    },
    {
      "id": "whisper-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 120,
      "y": 685,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 30,
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "❌ Whisper Tiny (V1 - Revised)",
      "strokeColor": "#c92a2a",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fontWeight": "bold"
    },
    {
      "id": "whisper-problems",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 120,
      "y": 720,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 130,
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "🔴 Architecture Failure: Autoregressive encoder-decoder\n   → Generates one token at a time, 2-4s post-utterance pause\n   → >1.5s latency = user thinks system didn't hear\n\n🔴 Training Data Failure: Heavy English/Latin-script bias\n   → Degrades on Hindi, Bhojpuri, Chhattisgarhi, coastal Tamil\n   → Word-error rates unusable for natural conversation\n\nV1 Section 6.1 decision RETIRED for elderly Indic users.",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent"
    },
    {
      "id": "indicconformer-box",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 100,
      "y": 885,
      "width": 700,
      "height": 200,
      "strokeColor": "#2b8a3e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "#d3f9d8",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roundness": {"type": 2, "value": 8}
    },
    {
      "id": "indicconformer-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 120,
      "y": 905,
      "width": 500,
      "height": 30,
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "✅ IndicConformer CTC-RNNT (AI4Bharat)",
      "strokeColor": "#2b8a3e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fontWeight": "bold"
    },
    {
      "id": "indicconformer-features",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 120,
      "y": 940,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 130,
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "🟢 Hybrid Decoding: Two paths simultaneously\n   CTC path: Non-autoregressive → word-by-word at sub-100ms (10× faster)\n   RNNT path: Autoregressive verification catches ambiguous phonemes\n\n🟢 Training: 22 constitutionally scheduled Indian languages\n   AI4Bharat Shrutilipi + IndicSUPERB datasets\n   Elderly speaker profiles, rural dialects, tier-2/3 city accents\n\n🟢 Edge Viability: Runs fully offline on low-end Android (4GB RAM)\nTimeline: G-02: 9-11 weeks (was 8-10, +2w Sherpa-ONNX eval)",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent"
    },
    {
      "id": "sherpa-box",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 820,
      "y": 665,
      "width": 700,
      "height": 200,
      "strokeColor": "#1864ab",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "#d0ebff",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roundness": {"type": 2, "value": 8}
    },
    {
      "id": "sherpa-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 840,
      "y": 685,
      "width": 550,
      "height": 30,
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "🔧 Runtime: Sherpa-ONNX vs. ONNX Direct",
      "strokeColor": "#1864ab",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fontWeight": "bold"
    },
    {
      "id": "sherpa-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 840,
      "y": 720,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 130,
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Sherpa-ONNX (Kaldi-based):\n✓ Non-autoregressive decoding (configurable)\n✓ Zero external dependencies, runs fully offline\n✓ Extensive model ecosystem for major Indian languages\n✓ Low streaming latency with non-autoregressive decoding\n\nNext Step (Weeks 1-2):Evaluate Sherpa-ONNX vs. direct ONNX Runtime\nTarget: Sub-200ms first-word latency for Tier-2/3 hardware (Redmi A3)\nFallback: Faster-Whisper for English (Power User tier)",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent"
    },
    {
      "id": "tts-box",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 820,
      "y": 885,
      "width": 700,
      "height": 200,
      "strokeColor": "#20c997",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "#d3f9d8",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roundness": {"type": 2, "value": 8}
    },
    {
      "id": "tts-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 840,
      "y": 905,
      "width": 500,
      "height": 30,
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "🆕 G-NEW-02: Indic TTS (3-4 weeks)",
      "strokeColor": "#087f5b",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fontWeight": "bold"
    },
    {
      "id": "tts-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 840,
      "y": 940,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 130,
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Primary: AI4Bharat Indic TTS (VITS architecture)\n✓ Natural prosody for 13 major Indian languages\n✓ On-device deployment for privacy\n✓ Regional pronunciation norms (not English phoneme transliteration)\n\nCloud Fallback: ElevenLabs Multilingual v3 / Google Chirp HD\n✓ For languages not covered by on-device model\n   Audio generated server-side, streamed → no raw voice transmitted\n\nElder Adaptation: 85% speaking rate default, user-adjustable in 10% increments",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent"
    },
    {
      "id": "readability-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 100,
      "y": 1110,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 35,
      "fontSize": 22,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "📚 Indic Language Readability: Why Flesch-Kincaid Fails",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fontWeight": "bold"
    },
    {
      "id": "readability-v1-ref",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 100,
      "y": 1150,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 25,
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "V1 Cross-Ref: Section 6.2 (Plain-Language), 9.1 → AD-11",
      "strokeColor": "#845ef7",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fontStyle": "italic"
    },
    {
      "id": "flesch-failure-box",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 100,
      "y": 1185,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 220,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffe3e3",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roundness": {"type": 2, "value": 8}
    },
    {
      "id": "flesch-failure-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 120,
      "y": 1205,
      "width": 700,
      "height": 30,
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "🔴 CRITICAL: Flesch-Kincaid Invalid for Indian Languages",
      "strokeColor": "#c92a2a",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fontWeight": "bold"
    },
    {
      "id": "flesch-failure-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 120,
      "y": 1240,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 150,
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Formula: Linear function of (avg sentence length) + (avg syllables per word)\nCalibrated on English lexicon. INVALID for Indian languages:\n\n🔴 Agglutinative (Tamil, Telugu, Kannada): Multiple morphemes → one word.\n   → English 7 words compress to 3 Tamil: longer = simpler (familiar morphemes)\n\n🔴 Juktakkhors (Bengali, Hindi): Consonant conjuncts = primary difficulty.\n   → High Juktakkhor density = harder to read (syllable count fails)\n\n🔴 Sandhi (Sanskrit-derived): Phonological merging at word boundaries.\n   → Confuses syllable-counting assuming stable word boundaries\n\nV1 Flesch-Kincaid to Hindi/Tamil would produce MEANINGLESS scores.",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent"
    },
    {
      "id": "language-models-box",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 920,
      "y": 1185,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 220,
      "strokeColor": "#2b8a3e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roundness": {"type": 2, "value": 8}
    },
    {
      "id": "language-models-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 940,
      "y": 1205,
      "width": 550,
      "height": 30,
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "✅ Language-Specific Regression Models",
      "strokeColor": "#2b8a3e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fontWeight": "bold"
    },
    {
      "id": "language-models-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 940,
      "y": 1240,
      "width": 560,
      "height": 150,
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "5 Language Families:\n\nHindi: Tatsama word density, modified ASL/AWL\nBengali: Juktakkhor frequency, bimorphemic compounds\nTamil: Morpheme-per-word ratio (not syllable count)\nTelugu/Kannada: Same morpheme approach (language-specific analysers)\nMarathi/Gujarati/Odia: Hybrid Devanagari + sandhi segmentation\n\nTool: AI4Bharat Indic NLP Library\nTimeline: G-03: 8-10 weeks (was 4-6, scope expanded 2×)",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent"
    },
    {
      "id": "postprocessor-box",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 920,
      "y": 1425,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 200,
      "strokeColor": "#1864ab",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "#d0ebff",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roundness": {"type": 2, "value": 8}
    },
    {
      "id": "postprocessor-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 940,
      "y": 1445,
      "width": 550,
      "height": 30,
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "🔧 3-Stage Post-Processor Pipeline",
      "strokeColor": "#1864ab",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fontWeight": "bold"
    },
    {
      "id": "postprocessor-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 940,
      "y": 1480,
      "width": 560,
      "height": 130,
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Stage 1: Language Detection (fastText <2MB)\n   Handles code-switched Hindi-English output\n\nStage 2: Language-Specific Scoring\n   AI4Bharat Indic NLP + regression coefficients\n   Cognitive load score (1-10): Elder=≤4\n\nStage 3: Conditional Simplification\n   Score>threshold → Haiku 4.5 simplification (30% of responses)\n   2-pass max → flag for human review if still above\n\nBenchmark: IndQA + IndicMMLU-Pro (Phase 1 go/no-go)",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent"
    }
  ],
